race.comment: Scratchings have decimated this field. ONE RUN WON (1) was good on debut at Kembla Grange when sticking on gamely into fourth. Is sure to have progressed from that and rates a leading player. TRUST YOUR CAPE (5) is a Hallowed Crown mare on debut for the Austin Camp. Has mixed her efforts in her lead-up but her most recent Warwick Farm trial placing inspires some confidence. Can play a major role in this small field. RUSKY RIPPER (7) disappointed when resuming at Narromine, over-racing in the early stages and the laying out under pressure in the straight. Better for the hitout and can improve sharply. MISHPAT (10) returns and looks next best.
